ARM: proc-v7.S: Add Cortex-A53 proc_info for AArch32 mode

The Cortex-A53 (MIDR 0x410fd03x) supports AArch32 at all exception
levels including EL1 (kernel). When running a 32-bit ARM kernel on
an ARMv8 SoC in AArch32 mode (e.g., Allwinner H6 without RMR switch),
the kernel needs a proc_info entry to properly initialize the CPU.

Without this patch, the A53 falls through to the generic __v7_proc_info
which does not set up SMP correctly for the core.

The A53 uses the same setup path as A7/A12/A15/A17 since it is a
multi-core ARMv8 processor where cache/TLB broadcasting is implicit.

--- a/arch/arm/mm/proc-v7.S
+++ b/arch/arm/mm/proc-v7.S
@@ -SETUP_LABELS
 __v7_ca7mp_setup:
 __v7_ca12mp_setup:
 __v7_ca15mp_setup:
 __v7_b15mp_setup:
 __v7_ca17mp_setup:
+__v7_ca53mp_setup:
 	do_invalidate_l1
 	mov	r10, #0

@@ -PROC_INFO_SECTION (after __v7_ca17mp_proc_info)

+	/*
+	 * ARM Ltd. Cortex A53 processor (in AArch32 mode).
+	 * MIDR: 0x410fd03x
+	 */
+	.type	__v7_ca53mp_proc_info, #object
+__v7_ca53mp_proc_info:
+	.long	0x410fd030
+	.long	0xff0ffff0
+	__v7_proc __v7_ca53mp_proc_info, __v7_ca53mp_setup, proc_fns = HARDENED_BPIALL_PROCESSOR_FUNCTIONS
+	.size	__v7_ca53mp_proc_info, . - __v7_ca53mp_proc_info
